text: Duhabi is a municipality in Sunsari District in the Koshi Zone of south- eastern Nepal. At the time of the 2001 Nepal census it had a population of 17,574. Duhabi is situated in between Itahari and Biratnagar, on the bank of Budi River. It is the center of Sunsari–Morang industrial corridor. == References == Category:Populated places in Sunsari District Category:Cities, towns and urban municipalities in Province No. 1 Category:Nepal municipalities established in 2014
